@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@
+## BMad Git Automation
+
+Use local automation to keep branch and commit history consistent during BMad work.
+
+### Commands
+```powershell
+powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\bmad-git.ps1 init -Slug "bmad-git-automation" -CreateBaselineCommit
+powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\bmad-git.ps1 commit -Slug "bmad-git-automation" -Phase "step-03" -Tag "auto"
+powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\bmad-git.ps1 self-check
+```
+
+### One-command auto wrapper
+```powershell
+# start work (branch + optional baseline commit)
+powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\bmad-auto.ps1 -Init -Slug "bmad-git-automation" -CreateBaselineCommit
+
+# commit by step alias
+powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\bmad-auto.ps1 -Slug "bmad-git-automation" -Step implement
+
+# or infer step from spec status
+powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\bmad-auto.ps1 -Slug "bmad-git-auto-management" -FromSpec
+```
+
+Step alias map: `plan -> step-02`, `implement -> step-03`, `review -> step-04`, `present -> step-05`.
+
+### Safety
+- No auto-push
+- No history rewrite
+- No destructive git commands
